# Trivy ignore file — suppress known false positives and legitimate operational requirements

# KSV-0014: readOnlyRootFilesystem
# Suppressed for stateful services that must write to the container filesystem:
# - backend: Python writes __pycache__ at import time
# - mongodb/redis: database engines write to temp dirs beyond their PVC mounts
# - grafana: writes to /tmp for rendering
# - loki/prometheus: write to /tmp for compaction/sort operations
# - promtail: writes /tmp/positions.yaml explicitly
KSV-0014

# KSV-0009, KSV-0010, KSV-0024, KSV-0121: node-exporter host access
# node-exporter DaemonSet requires hostNetwork, hostPID, hostPorts, and
# read-only hostPath mounts (/proc, /sys, /) to collect system-level metrics.
# These are standard requirements for the prom/node-exporter image.
KSV-0009
KSV-0010
KSV-0024
KSV-0121

# KSV-0118: default security context (node-exporter, promtail)
# node-exporter and promtail are infrastructure DaemonSets with elevated
# host access requirements. Security contexts are explicitly set where possible
# but some checks fire at the DaemonSet level due to host access requirements.
KSV-0118

# KSV-0047: Role permits privilege escalation from node proxy
# Required by prometheus and promtail for scraping kubelet metrics (/metrics,
# /metrics/cadvisor) via the Kubernetes API node proxy. Standard for
# in-cluster Prometheus deployments.
KSV-0047

# DS-0002: Dockerfile USER — claude-code-api external repo
# claude-code-api is an external dependency cloned from GitHub. Its Dockerfile
# is not maintained by this project. Suppressed to avoid blocking CI on
# third-party code we do not control.
DS-0002

# CVE-2026-25210: libexpat1 — no fix available in Debian 13
# Information disclosure in libexpat. No Debian package fix exists yet.
# Upstream fix must be backported by the Debian security team.
CVE-2026-25210

# CVE-2022-4055: xdg-utils — fix_deferred in Debian
# Improper parse of mailto URIs. Debian has deferred this fix.
# xdg-utils is required by Playwright/Chromium for browser launch support.
CVE-2022-4055

# CVE-2026-23949: jaraco.context — base image pip build tool, not used at runtime
# jaraco.context is a transitive dep of pip's build backend in python:3.11-slim.
# Our app uses uv (not pip) at build time. This tool is never invoked at runtime.
CVE-2026-23949

# CVE-2026-24049: wheel — base image pip build tool, not used at runtime
# wheel is installed in the base Python image for bootstrapping pip.
# Our Dockerfile now uses uv for all package installation, bypassing wheel entirely.
# wheel is never invoked at runtime in the production container.
CVE-2026-24049

# CVE-2026-24882: GnuPG dirmngr — stack-based buffer overflow in tpm2daemon
# dirmngr is installed as a dependency of the Debian base image. We do not use
# TPM2 or GnuPG at runtime. No Debian fix available yet.
CVE-2026-24882

# CPython 3.13 system packages — Debian base image, no fix available
# These affect the Debian-packaged Python 3.13 (libpython3.13, python3.13-minimal),
# NOT the Python 3.11 our app actually runs. They exist because python:3.11-slim
# is built on Debian 13 which ships Python 3.13 as the system interpreter.
# None of these modules (http.client buffering, IMAP/POP3 injection, tarfile,
# email headers) are exploitable through our application.
CVE-2025-13836
CVE-2025-15366
CVE-2025-15367
CVE-2025-8194
CVE-2026-1299

# Go stdlib CVEs in Playwright's bundled Chromium/driver binary
# These affect Go's crypto/tls, archive/tar, net/url, archive/zip, crypto/x509.
# Playwright bundles a Go binary we don't control; fix requires upstream Playwright update.
# Not exploitable through our application (we don't use Go directly).
CVE-2025-68121
CVE-2025-58183
CVE-2025-61726
CVE-2025-61728
CVE-2025-61729
CVE-2026-25679
